As Shelia wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/25/2004 at 08:16:09 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>At his birthday party, Mr. Green would not directly tell how old he 
>was. He said, If you add the year of my birth to this year, subtract 
>the year of my tenth birthday and the year of my fiftieth birthday , 
>and then add my present age, the result is eighty, How old was Mr. 
>Green. (December 14,1997)
>
>[Difficulty]
>I don't know where to start to figure out the age. I know that the 
>party was on December 14, 1997.
>
>[Thoughts]
>I would start at 1997 and then add one year. Then I don't know where 
>else to figure out the problem.

Hello Sheila,

Letting y be birth year, 

y+1997 - (y+10) - (y+50) + (1997-y) = 80

Solving this gives y=1927.  So 1997-1927=70.



